1
00:00:11,467 --> 00:00:16,233
I just want to know if the
medicines you give me are safe.

2
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:17,467
Do you really think

3
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:20,800
I'll give you a medicine
that can harm you?

4
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:24,267
Get checked by a licensed
doctor to know the truth.

5
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:25,800
She's already suspecting.

6
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:28,900
Stop giving her medicines
she doesn't need.

7
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:30,833
They said it was a gray car.

8
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,233
I remember it now.

9
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:34,600
The woman who took Kayla
was also riding a gray car.

10
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:35,733
Remember, Olive.

11
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:38,233
We both have the right
to sell that house.

12
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:40,633
Don't you ever try me, Jade!

13
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:43,533
Hello. I want to get checked.

14
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:46,633
I want to know
if I'm really sick.

15
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:47,700
What are you doing there?

16
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:50,667
We only want to know
who owns that house.

17
00:00:50,733 --> 00:00:52,800
Are they also the owner in 2007?

18
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:53,633
Where are they now?

19
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:55,967
Leave, or I'll call the cops.

20
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:49,833
Who are they, Mr. Ando?

21
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,333
Are they buyers?

22
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:56,133
Or did my darn sister send
them to check the property?

23
00:01:56,967 --> 00:01:58,533
I think they are thieves, Ma'am.

24
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:02,300
As if they could get anything
from this place.

25
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,233
Okay.

26
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:09,267
I'll just get the title inside
to ensure Jade won't get it.

27
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:16,600
Hello, Obet?

28
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,700
Hello, Ma'am Olive.

29
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:26,033
Ma'am Mookie is in Immaculate
Heart Pediatric Hospital.

30
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:27,400
What?

31
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,567
Are you sure?
Yes.

32
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:34,233
She's with a man her age.

33
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:34,767
Okay.

34
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,333
Mr. Ando, here's the key.

35
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,100
The land title is in my room.

36
00:02:40,167 --> 00:02:41,167
Please get it.

37
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,033
Keep it.

38
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:46,200
Make sure Jade won't get it.

39
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:47,233
Yes, Ma'am.

40
00:02:56,267 --> 00:02:57,400
Are you okay, Mookie?

41
00:03:01,133 --> 00:03:02,433
I'm nervous.

42
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:17,000
Do you think this is right?

43
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:25,800
I'm thinking maybe
I'm being impulsive.

44
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
I'm disobeying my mom again.

45
00:03:29,733 --> 00:03:31,367
We can back out if you like.

46
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:37,633
But you only want to know
the truth, right?

47
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:45,567
It's so difficult.

48
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,800
I feel like I'm betraying
my mom.

49
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:58,133
But I also won't be able to rest
until I find out the truth.

50
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:04,733
No.

51
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,200
I'm already here.

52
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,100
I will get this done.

53
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:25,167
- Here's your phone.
- Oh, yeah.

54
00:04:25,767 --> 00:04:27,267
- Here.
- Thank you.

55
00:04:28,867 --> 00:04:29,967
Here.

56
00:04:30,033 --> 00:04:30,967
This is my other phone.

57
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:32,267
The one you called.

58
00:04:32,967 --> 00:04:34,233
I don't use it anymore.

59
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:35,567
So you can have it.

60
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:38,433
So we can talk.

61
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,333
Really?

62
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,200
Of course.

63
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,433
Thank you, Zayn.

64
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,667
You are so kind.

65
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:02,167
Maria Angela Caparas?

66
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:03,067
That's you, Mookie.

67
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:04,567
Let's go.

68
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:08,333
Slowly.

69
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:16,500
Come on.

70
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:18,167
Are you okay?

71
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:25,433
I'm getting nervous.

72
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:36,100
Didn't I tell you not
to let Mookie out?

73
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:39,267
Sorry, Ma'am, she escaped
from me again.

74
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:41,300
Brace yourself when I return!

75
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:51,467
Oh, look, bestie.

76
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:54,600
What are you praying for, BFF?

77
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:59,100
Are you praying to win
the Big Two tournament?

78
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,867
Shut up.

79
00:06:01,933 --> 00:06:03,267
I'm busy with the Lord.

80
00:06:03,333 --> 00:06:04,467
Are you close with him?

81
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:08,067
Oh, Lord.

82
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:09,833
I'm sorry.

83
00:06:11,167 --> 00:06:14,033
Your enemy sent his underling.

84
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,133
Excuse me.

85
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,500
Wow, underling?

86
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:22,033
We only want to know
what you prayed for.

87
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:22,800
Yeah.

88
00:06:23,867 --> 00:06:27,300
I prayed to find my grandchild.

89
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:35,467
Your family's life story
is like a drama series.

90
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,733
Twins are given away.

91
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:41,000
A child is missing.

92
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:46,667
You and Emma are both
longing for your children.

93
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:49,933
I know how Emma feels.

94
00:06:52,733 --> 00:06:56,633
I know how she longs
to see her daughter.

95
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,133
Because I feel the same.

96
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:05,133
I'm longing to see my twins.

97
00:07:07,067 --> 00:07:07,967
It's painful.

98
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:15,267
But Emma feels twice the pain.

99
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:18,367
I gave my twins away,

100
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:22,267
but her daughter Kayla
was taken away from her.

101
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:23,900
And I...

102
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:28,400
still have Emma
when I lost the twins.

103
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:30,100
But, Emma...

104
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:41,367
You're so annoying.

105
00:07:41,433 --> 00:07:43,900
I was so focused on praying.

106
00:07:43,967 --> 00:07:45,900
And you did that.

107
00:07:45,967 --> 00:07:47,800
It's her fault.
She has so many questions.

108
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:50,633
I assume this is medicine
for lupus.

109
00:07:57,567 --> 00:08:00,167
Yes, I was told it
was lupus medicines.

110
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:06,300
But Doc, won't you feel weak

111
00:08:06,367 --> 00:08:11,833
if you keep taking medicines
even without any illnesses?

112
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:14,300
And isn't it bad
for the health?

113
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:15,467
Of course.

114
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:21,100
Medicines for autoimmune disease
can damage your eyesight.

115
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:25,233
And patients can contract
other diseases

116
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:27,800
like diabetes and osteoporosis.

117
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,500
Really, Doctor?

118
00:08:30,467 --> 00:08:32,467
I don't want to contract
those illnesses.

119
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:35,533
Mookie?

120
00:08:36,167 --> 00:08:37,300
Mommy?

121
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:47,800
I'll donate money to the church,
even if it isn't much.

122
00:08:48,133 --> 00:08:49,467
You're going to donate?

123
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:50,700
Yes!

124
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:51,767
Yes.

125
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:55,867
BFF, are these your twins?

126
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:56,833
That's right.

127
00:08:58,767 --> 00:09:01,600
This is Elsa, and this is Eva.

128
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:04,067
This, this.

129
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,267
Elsa.

130
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:07,100
Why does she have a bandage?

131
00:09:07,167 --> 00:09:07,867
I'm also curious.

132
00:09:12,033 --> 00:09:13,167
Eva?

133
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:14,500
Eva, dear.

134
00:09:14,567 --> 00:09:16,100
What's the matter?

135
00:09:18,133 --> 00:09:20,133
Please stop, Eva.

136
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:22,200
Here.

137
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:23,933
Here's your milk.

138
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:31,200
Elsa!

139
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,800
Elsa!

140
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:50,433
Whenever I remember that,

141
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:54,700
I feel it was right
to give them away because...

142
00:09:56,267 --> 00:09:58,133
I'm not a good mother.

143
00:09:58,867 --> 00:09:59,533
Hey!

144
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,100
Don't say that.

145
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:04,000
It's not easy to care
for a child, let alone twins.

146
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:05,067
She's right.

147
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:09,133
And you've been the
best mother to Emma.

148
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,033
Okay? Remember that.

149
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,900
The best, my foot.

150
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:14,533
Fighting is our hobby.

151
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,800
It's normal.

152
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:17,700
That's your way of showing love.

153
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:20,833
And Emma wouldn't
be a good person

154
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,700
if you weren't a good mother
to her.

155
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:25,867
So, you're a good mother.

156
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:26,800
Okay?

157
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:28,833
It's just not that obvious.

158
00:10:29,933 --> 00:10:35,133
And I'm sure once they
find Baby Kayla,

159
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:38,267
you'll also be the best
grandmother.

160
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:39,000
Right.

161
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,167
I'd love that.

162
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,300
I want to become a grandmother.

163
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:50,100
I wonder where's
my granddaughter now.

164
00:10:54,267 --> 00:10:55,033
Mookie!

165
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,467
Mookie, sweetie,
what are you doing here?

166
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:02,567
Doc, I'm so sorry

167
00:11:02,633 --> 00:11:04,900
my daughter wasted your time
for this nonsense.

168
00:11:04,967 --> 00:11:06,567
Let's go, dear. Let's go home.
Let's go.

169
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:07,467
- Mommy, no!
- Let's go home.

170
00:11:07,533 --> 00:11:08,800
- Mommy, no!
- Come on.

171
00:11:09,433 --> 00:11:10,567
I don't want to, Mommy.

172
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:11,800
- Let's go.
- Please.

173
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:13,567
- Don't be stubborn, Mookie.
- Mommy, I don't want to.

174
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:16,167
- Let's go home.
- I don't want to, Mommy!

175
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:17,000
Come on, let's go.
- Let's go.
- Mommy, no!

176
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,200
Doc, I'm so sorry for this.

177
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:20,133
- Mommy!
- Let's go.

178
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,433
- Mommy!
- Let's go, Mookie. Get up.

179
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:21,900
Mommy!

180
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,633
Mommy, please.

181
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:25,033
- Mookie!
- Mommy!

182
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:25,800
Mommy!

183
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:26,867
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

184
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:27,500
Mookie.

185
00:11:27,567 --> 00:11:28,700
- Mookie.
- Mookie!

186
00:11:29,733 --> 00:11:30,667
- Mookie!
- Mookie.

187
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:32,133
Doc. Mookie!

188
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,000
Mookie!

189
00:11:35,433 --> 00:11:36,233
Mookie!

190
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:53,100
You love your daughter so much.

191
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:56,167
Yes.

192
00:11:57,767 --> 00:12:01,967
That's why I was so disheartened
to hear all this.

193
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:08,667
That she's not convinced
she's sick.

194
00:12:09,667 --> 00:12:14,167
And now I heard she's not
taking her medicines.

195
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:20,533
What if her organs
suddenly fail?

196
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:26,733
Mommy.

197
00:12:30,267 --> 00:12:36,533
I only want to know
if I'm really sick.

198
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:38,967
Believe me, Doc.

199
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:44,767
I feel weaker when
I take the medicines.

200
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:00,333
How are you feeling now?

201
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:03,767
Doc...

202
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:08,800
my pediatrician told me
I wasn't sick.

203
00:13:10,367 --> 00:13:16,067
That's why I want to get
tested to know the truth.

204
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:16,933
Mookie.

205
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,567
Didn't I already explain
to you everything

206
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:21,100
that Doc Charles said?

207
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:23,067
Let's go.

208
00:13:23,133 --> 00:13:24,133
Let's go home.

209
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:26,133
- Mommy, no.
- Let's go home.

210
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,200
No, Mommy.

211
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:29,000
Mommy, please.

212
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Please, Mommy, have me tested.

213
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:37,367
I will do everything you want...

214
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:42,167
once I see that I'm really sick.

215
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,067
Please, Mommy.

216
00:13:46,067 --> 00:13:46,600
Please?

217
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:03,200
Okay.

218
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:10,467
Please run all the
necessary tests for my daughter.

219
00:14:41,733 --> 00:14:44,000
Let Maria Angela rest
for a few minutes,

220
00:14:44,067 --> 00:14:45,700
then you can go home.

221
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:49,333
I'll call you once
the results are out.

222
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:51,100
Thank you, Doc.

223
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:16,467
Looks like the caretaker
won't leave.

224
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:38,833
Mom?

225
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:39,833
Hello, dear?

226
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:41,600
Is there any news?

227
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:44,333
We can't get in.

228
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,667
The caretaker is still here.

229
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:51,500
I prayed for you earlier.

230
00:15:52,267 --> 00:15:53,000
Yes.

231
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:54,767
I made a deal with God.

232
00:15:54,833 --> 00:16:03,167
I told Him I wouldn't
insist on finding my twin,

233
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:07,700
but I asked Him
to take care of them.

234
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:14,467
And I also asked Him
to grant your wish.

235
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:17,000
I ask Him to bring
Kayla back to you.

236
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:17,800
That's it.

237
00:16:18,533 --> 00:16:20,067
Mom, thank you.

238
00:16:20,133 --> 00:16:23,400
Let's both pray to find
our children.

239
00:16:25,167 --> 00:16:27,867
Because I also want
to see my sibling.

240
00:16:27,933 --> 00:16:29,300
It's impossible, dear.

241
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:34,800
Ma'am Alice said she didn't
have any information

242
00:16:34,867 --> 00:16:38,233
about the person who adopted
your sibling.

243
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,633
That's hopeless.

244
00:16:48,767 --> 00:16:49,933
Mom, please stop crying.

245
00:16:54,533 --> 00:16:55,500
Dear.

246
00:17:03,733 --> 00:17:07,233
Flor, I'm sorry.

247
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:10,767
No, it's okay, even
if I get fired.

248
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:12,533
Don't worry.

249
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:17,533
Flor.

250
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:19,000
Yes, Ma'am.
Leave.

251
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:23,200
Yes, Ma'am, I've already
packed my bags.

252
00:17:25,133 --> 00:17:27,367
What I meant is to leave
Mookie and me for a while.

253
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:29,833
I'm not firing you.

254
00:17:33,633 --> 00:17:35,967
Thank you, Ma'am.

255
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,500
I hope you're happy now.

256
00:17:54,533 --> 00:17:56,800
I hope you're happy with
what you did to me.

257
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:00,600
You betrayed me.

258
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:03,733
You humiliated me...

259
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,833
in front of my fellow doctor.

260
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:10,267
But I guess...

261
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:14,133
what happened
really had to happen.

262
00:18:17,133 --> 00:18:20,433
So I can realize my mistakes.

263
00:18:25,133 --> 00:18:26,233
You know, Mookie...

264
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:32,567
I know
I'm not a perfect mom.

265
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,467
But everything I do...

266
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,333
is for you.

267
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:46,300
Once your test results
come out,

268
00:18:48,567 --> 00:18:49,767
you'll realize...

269
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:58,233
I do all this to protect you.

270
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,867
The man is still there.

271
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,467
Should we look for
somewhere to eat?

272
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,667
Let's go back later.

273
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,000
Okay.

274
00:19:54,233 --> 00:19:54,700
Dan.

275
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:56,267
That's him.

276
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:13,700
He's gone.

277
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:15,400
Let's go.

278
00:20:23,233 --> 00:20:24,933
I'll look at the cars.

279
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:50,700
Dan!

280
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:52,567
What?
A motorcycle is coming.

281
00:20:53,567 --> 00:20:54,667
Maybe it's the caretaker!

282
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:57,033
Come on.

283
00:20:58,667 --> 00:20:59,733
He's back.

284
00:21:01,433 --> 00:21:02,567
I knew it.

285
00:21:04,733 --> 00:21:06,200
Hello, Dr. Villanueva.

286
00:21:06,267 --> 00:21:07,900
Are Mookie's test
results ready?

287
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:09,500
Good.
I'll see you.

288
00:21:10,567 --> 00:21:11,900
I just have to drop
by somewhere first.

289
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:20,600
What the!

290
00:21:21,667 --> 00:21:24,500
Why did this car
have to act up now!

291
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,233
Flor, hurry! Stop that taxi!

292
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:33,200
Okay, Ma'am.

293
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:34,233
Wait.

294
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:35,233
Taxi!

295
00:21:35,867 --> 00:21:37,333
Mister! Taxi!

296
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,067
I knew it. You're thieves.

297
00:21:42,167 --> 00:21:43,767
- No. You're mistaken.
- No.

298
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:44,633
What do you mean by no?

299
00:21:45,167 --> 00:21:46,067
Mister, wait.

300
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:47,100
Mister!

301
00:21:47,167 --> 00:21:47,733
Dan!

302
00:21:48,567 --> 00:21:49,500
Stop!
That's enough!

303
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:51,200
Stop!

304
00:21:54,533 --> 00:21:56,900
Your test results are out.

305
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:58,133
It's confirmed.

306
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,800
You have an autoimmune
disease and leukemia.

307
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:03,100
I know it's hard to accept it.

308
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:04,933
That's why I'm here for you.

309
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,667
I will take care of you, dear.

310
00:22:06,733 --> 00:22:07,367
Miss, Miss!

311
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:08,500
Your receipt.

312
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:11,967
Hello, Danilo.

313
00:22:12,033 --> 00:22:14,900
The woman who took
your child is here!

314
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:15,767
- What?
- What?

315
00:22:15,833 --> 00:22:17,700
We'll get through this, sweetie.

316
00:22:17,767 --> 00:22:19,167
I won't leave you.

317
00:22:19,233 --> 00:22:24,133
I saw her face after
giving me medicines.

318
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:24,833
I think...

319
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:27,133
she faked the results.

320
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,100
Tell me any favor you need.

321
00:22:29,167 --> 00:22:30,833
I'll do it for you.

322
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:34,433
I hope one day, Mookie
finds out she isn't sick.

323
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:38,033
That you've just made
everything up.

324
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:40,733
Mookie, I've found
your test results!

325
00:22:41,433 --> 00:22:42,500
What does it say?
